{
  "page": "Lord of Stonedance",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Lord of Stonedance</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> is a title held by the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Massey\" title=\"House Massey\">House Massey</a>, the ruler of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stonedance\" title=\"Stonedance\">Stonedance</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The current Lord of Stonedance is unknown.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Crownlands.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The crownlands and the location of Stonedance\"><img alt=\"The crownlands and the location of Stonedance\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Crownlands.png/400px-Crownlands.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/26/Crownlands.png/600px-Crownlands.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/26/Crownlands.png/800px-Crownlands.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 65.6%; left: 79.4%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -5px; top: -5px; width: 10px; font-size: 10px;\"><img alt=\"The crownlands and the location of Stonedance\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/10px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Stonedance\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/15px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/20px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 100%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; left: 0.5em; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"><b>Stonedance</b></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a> and the location of Stonedance\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><table>\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Stonedance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Maldon_Massey\" title=\"Maldon Massey\">Maldon Massey</a> built <a href=\"/index.php/Stonedance\" title=\"Stonedance\">Stonedance</a> and ruled <a href=\"/index.php/Massey%27s_Hook\" title=\"Massey&#39;s Hook\">Massey's Hook</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>. The Masseys broke away from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Durwald_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Durwald I Durrandon\">Durwald the Fat</a> and declared themselves kings, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> King <a href=\"/index.php/Josua_Massey\" title=\"Josua Massey\">Josua Massey</a> was the last Massey king, his son was made a puppet lord under the rule of King <a href=\"/index.php/Togarion_Bar_Emmon\" title=\"Togarion Bar Emmon\">Togarion Bar Emmon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prior to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, House Massey was sworn to House Durrandon of <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> but had closer ties to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> of nearby <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. When <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon the Conqueror</a> launched his <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">invasion</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Triston_Massey\" title=\"Triston Massey\">Triston Massey</a> supported him instead of the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Argilac_Durrandon\" title=\"Argilac Durrandon\">Argilac the Arrogant</a>. Aegon later made him his <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_laws\" title=\"Master of laws\">master of laws</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lucifer_Massey\" title=\"Lucifer Massey\">Lucifer Massey</a> stood for King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a> in his <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_of_seven\" title=\"Trial of seven\">trial of seven</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/42_AC\" title=\"42 AC\">42&#160;AC</a>, and was killed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Warrior%27s_Son\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Warrior&#39;s Son\">Warrior's Son</a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harys_Horpe\" title=\"Harys Horpe\">Harys Horpe</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/47_AC\" title=\"47 AC\">47&#160;AC</a>, Lord Massey and his two eldest sons died of a fever. He was succeeded by his third son, <a href=\"/index.php/Albin_Massey\" title=\"Albin Massey\">Albin Massey</a>. Three years later, King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> named Albin his new <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_laws\" title=\"Master of laws\">master of laws</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Justiciar\" title=\"Justiciar\">justiciar</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Lord Albin died in the winter of <a href=\"/index.php/59_AC\" title=\"59 AC\">59&#160;AC</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Shivers\" title=\"Shivers\">Shivers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gormon_Massey\" title=\"Gormon Massey\">Gormon Massey</a> was killed attempting to tame <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone_(island)\" title=\"Dragonstone (island)\">Dragonstone</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Lords_of_Stonedance\">Known Lords of Stonedance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_of_Stonedance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Lords of Stonedance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Maldon_Massey\" title=\"Maldon Massey\">Maldon Massey</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The son of King <a href=\"/index.php/Josua_Massey\" title=\"Josua Massey\">Josua Massey</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Triston_Massey\" title=\"Triston Massey\">Triston Massey</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lucifer_Massey\" title=\"Lucifer Massey\">Lucifer Massey</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord Massey, who died from a fever in <a href=\"/index.php/47_AC\" title=\"47 AC\">47&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Albin_Massey\" title=\"Albin Massey\">Albin Massey</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class